&gt; &gt; Is there a way to get each test method to run in it&#39;s own JVM? I am
&gt; &gt; finding that setUp and tearDown are not enough. I have a lot of code 
&gt; &gt; that has to reset static state such as caches each time a test is 
&gt; &gt; run, code that is only needed for unit testing. If each test method 
&gt; &gt; ran in it&#39;s own JVM, my testing code would not require me to make 
&gt; &gt; changes in the code I am testing.
&gt; &gt; 
&gt; &gt; It&#39;s not just singletons but also caches that should be initialized
&gt; &gt; once for a JVM. And, honestly, if you think about it, each test 
&gt; &gt; method SHOULD be atomic. Mock objects seemed kind of like a kludge 
&gt; &gt; for tests not being run atomically.
&gt; &gt; 
&gt; 
&gt; I guess using the swingui reloading classloader on a per test method
&gt; basis
&gt; would do the trick.
